caption: Ordered takeout, strolled around and picked up a few more food items while we waited. Love that they cool the katsu before packing it so it doesn't get soggy. GENIUS! One of the best vendors in OHM! My new favorite katsu place!!

Delicious pork katsu made with layered pork (instead of just pork cutlet like most other places...) Crunchy on the outside and very moist on the inside, scrumptious! Owners are very nice and serving size is excellent, highly recommend!
They don’t understand demand and supply. Always no food prepared and return the customers.
Tender inside Crispy outside! Price right good katsu!
Walk in order at 10:40 2 bento's ready at 11:35. Best to order ahead. Walked around during the wait. The tonkatsu was light and not greasy.

So went to Oahana Marketplace and decided to give this place a try as I love my katsu.  Now their bento is premade so it's not freshly fried up. I consider that a disappointment as katsu is best freshly made and hot. Having said that...their tonkatsu is AWESOME! I can't believe how good and flaky this thing is! If I had to compare it I would say it compares to Tonkatsu Tamafuji. Is it as good? NO. But it gets closer than just about any other katsu place I've tried all for a relatively cheap price for the quality you get. The bento is $15 and for an extra 10 you get double the tonkatsu.  The bento comes with ground sesame seeds, katsu sauce, potato salad, cooked edamame, piece of kombucha and really good quality rice with an ume.  I have heard that they can and do run out but you can order online so that's probably the way to go.

Due to flight delay + having my own car, I was finally able to try this place before I leave HNL. I have bookmarked this place for quite some time and been curious to try their multi-layer tonkatsu since Kimukatsu in Honolulu closed. It did not disappoint.  Juicy tonkatsu with right amount of seasoning and great panko.  Side dishes were simple yet delicious too.  Kabocha and Hijime were yummy, great pick of rice too, very moist and fluffy.   It bothers me a lot when restaurants picked wrong crop of rice which did not happen here.  I was able to obtain one last bento box with last minute walk-in, thanks for workers there!  I will def. make reservation next time when I am in town.  Tip - eat their bento box ASAP as dine in is no longer possible here.
Amazing layered pork tonkatsu! Check their instagram for latest hours - text or call to reserve your order.

Very pleasant front counter person. Ordered a katsu bento. It was delicious.The pork seemed to be slice thin and reassemble. This made it tender and juicy.Thanks to Donna O and Nadine C had a great lunch. Will be back.Be safe and support local.

It's authentic japanese Katsu fried pork place. Looks very cool, the japanese lady is very friendly and cute. You must make a reservation for the Tonkatsu bento lunch plates, otherwise you can't walk in and get the food. It's always  sold out, 24/7 order online. They also have Japanese snacks, desserts, beverage. I want to try the mont blanc next time!! It's in Ohana Hale marcket place.
